overview: The user initiated a project to enhance a sleep questionnaire
  application by integrating a database for response storage and developing an
  admin dashboard for data access. After evaluating the existing codebase, it
  was determined that a new database model for questionnaire responses, API
  endpoints for data management, and an authentication system for the dashboard
  were required. The user opted for a simple password-based authentication and a
  combined approach for demographic data collection (year of birth, sex,
  zipcode, weight, height). The implementation involved updating data types and
  validation schemas, creating a Prisma model for ,
  developing API routes for saving, retrieving, and exporting data as CSV, and
  building a login page and a dashboard UI. A lightweight session management
  system using signed HTTP-only cookies was also put in place. The questionnaire
  form was modified to submit data to the new database endpoint. All specified
  components were successfully integrated, providing a complete solution for
  data persistence and client access.
